  "text": "Protein expression levels were determined by western blotting analysis. Equal amount of protein samples were separated on a 10% SDS-polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis and transferred onto a PVDF membrane (Bio-Rad). After blocking with 5% skim milk in Trisbuffered saline containing 0.1% Tween-20 (TBS-T) for 1 h, membrane was incubated with primary antibody overnight at 4 o C, and probed with appropriate secondary antibody conjugated with horseradish peroxidase (Cell signaling Technology) for 1 h at RT. Bolts were detected using enhanced chamiluminescence (ECL) reagents (BioRad, Hercules, CA) [CITATION_1] .",
